      <description>&lt;div&gt;I am just wondering why caster spells (int for sure but probably wis casters as well) cost so much in the bazaar?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;My problem is this... I have limited time to play this game during the week.  I enjoy the game, I like the game, I would like to continue playing the game.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;So why on earth (or norrath) does SOE make caster progression so difficult at 65+ level??  I have managed to get into a few groups where the muramite runes 'supposedly' drop but, guess what, none have dropped.  I have this thing called a real life (or RL) in game terms and do not have the time to play like many of the other players do so I can't group every single day and pray that I get lucky and have a rune drop.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;The other side of the coin is that I could go and buy them in the bazaar... at 15000pp the lowest price I saw the other night for a 'something' muramite rune.  I know that you can get lucky and I have heard of them selling for around 5k but I also do not have thousands of platinum sitting in the bank.  I guess SOE's plan is to help keep all those plat sellers in business even though they say that they disprove of the plat sellers.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;So the end result is that I pretty much cannot get any of my 66 and higher spells what with being a casual player and lack of pp.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Fine and dandy... this is just the free market in EQ happening and I respect that.  SOE has greatly limited rune drops that folk can sell them at gross prices (some more gross than others).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;The end result of this, in my case, though is that there is a new expansion coming out (PoR) that I have absolutely no reason to bother buying because SOE and certainly   a minority of a greedy player base have made it impossible for a casual player like myself to advance past 66.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Actually, thanks to double xp, I am now lvl 70 but with lvl 65 spells.  I could perhaps buy 2 higher spells if I can find some around 4k each at most.  After that, I either buy plat online or end up just giving up on EQ.  Its a shame really because I just came back to it after a year absence and was really enjoying it until running into this wall.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Its not like all players, not just casters, don't have other difficult goals to reach like AA's / Epics / etc.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Please increase drop rates, SOE, so casual players don't have to give up.  All I want are my basic core abilities as I level... I am willing to struggle for anything else!&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
